  <summary>7/28/1987--Introduced.
Requires Class A motor fuel sold after 1987 for motor vehicles in the District of Columbia to have at least a two percent oxygen content by weight. Terminates such requirement when the District of Columbia certifies that it has attained the national ambient air quality standard for carbon monoxide.</summary>
